    "body": "### Problem\n\nWhen I try to re-open a file with `:restart` command, I sometimes met this error:\n\n> Error in UIEnter Autocommands for \"*\":                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                         \nE5107: Lua: [string \":lua\"]:1: unexpected symbol near '/' \n\n\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nUnfortunately, this is not 100% reproducible and seems random. Sometime, I was able to reproduce with:\n\n```\nnvim --clean lua/some_file.lua\n```\n\nThen try to re-load the file with `:restart` command: `:restart e lua/some_file.lua`.\nWith high probability, I see the above error message.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nI should be able to re-open the file, without such error.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.12.0\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nnot applicable\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nmacOS 26.3.1\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nghostty 1.3.1\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-ghostty\n\n### Installation\n\nhomebrew",
